  "course_description": "Studies in poetry and poetic forms. Readings may vary in individual sections, but all sections emphasize critical reading and writing about poetic art. Required for English majors.",
  "course_notes": "This course begins with the fundamentals of poetry: diction, imagery, figurative language, symbolism, prosody, poetic forms, vers libre, and so on. In addition, the course considers poetry's role as persuasive rhetoric in the new social movements of contemporary public culture. Finally, this section will enhance discussions of poetry's relation to the pictorial arts as well as poetry's performative dimension as a spoken art. Course Requirements: on-line journaling, three out-of-class essays, and a final exam.",
